radiographic_examinations.findings: The right subclavian PICC line has been redirected with the tip now in the superior portion of the SVC. There is tortuosity of the aorta, but the lungs are clear without vascular congestion or definite pleural effusion. Mild blunting of the left costophrenic angle is seen, possibly related to either small pleural effusion or prior pleural thickening.
